# Solentra — Cursor Rules

## Project
Solentra is an AI-first EHR built on Medplum v5.1.6 (FHIR, React, TypeScript, Mantine v8).
Owner: Logan Carton, Psychiatric NP. Built for a real clinical practice.

## Key Files
- `packages/app/src/solentra/ProviderDashboard.tsx` — main dashboard (floating windows)
- `packages/app/src/solentra/PatientChart.tsx` — patient chart with tabs
- `packages/app/src/solentra/VisitNote.tsx` — visit note writer
- `packages/app/src/solentra/clinicalAlerts.ts` — BPA rules engine
- `packages/app/src/solentra/dashboardData.ts` — FHIR dashboard data hook
- `packages/app/src/solentra/patientData.ts` — FHIR patient record hook
- `packages/app/src/AppRoutes.tsx` — routes

## Rules — Follow Every Time

### No Bloat (highest priority)
- NEVER create a new file if an existing file is the right place. Add to the existing file.
- NEVER leave old code in place when replacing it. Delete the old implementation entirely — types, constants, functions, JSX, mock data, all of it.
- NEVER append new code below old code to "override" it. Replace it.
- NEVER duplicate type definitions across files. Define once, import everywhere.
- NEVER create a helper or abstraction for a single use case.
- If two files contain the same data or type, consolidate into one and delete the other.

### Code Quality
- No dead code. No commented-out blocks. No "old version" kept around.
- No wrapper components that just pass props through.
- No speculative features — only build what was asked.
- No error handling for scenarios that can't happen.
- No docstrings or comments on code you didn't write.

### TypeScript
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit -p packages/app/tsconfig.json` before finishing.
- Fix all type errors before considering a task done.
- Never use `any` — use proper types or `unknown`.

### Git
- Never push with TypeScript errors.
- Never amend existing commits.
- Write meaningful commit messages describing what changed and why.
- Never commit .env files or secrets.

### Stack-Specific
- UI: Mantine v8 only. No other UI libraries.
- Icons: @tabler/icons-react only.
- Routing: react-router v6.
- FHIR: use Medplum hooks (useSearchResources, useSearchOne) — don't fetch manually.
- Demo data fallback pattern: live FHIR data when available, mock data otherwise. Keep both paths working.
